The paper deals with the problem of preprocessing a string and answering queries about the frequency of elements in a range. This is a classic problem in data structures and falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses compressed space solutions, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC). The problem of range majority and minority involves counting and frequency, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses information theory and entropy, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper discusses query time and optimization, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG).
